## Configuration constants (top of the script)

| Constant | What it should be set to |
|---|---|
| `WRAPPER_ID_PREFIX` | The prefix of the ID Attribute you gave the Tiptap input element (before the row index number) |
| `MENU_ID_PREFIX` | The prefix of the ID Attribute you gave your custom menu element (before the row index number) |
| `BOUNDS_GROUP_ID_PREFIX` | The prefix of the ID Attribute of the element the menu should stay within horizontally. Currently set the same as `WRAPPER_ID_PREFIX` (menu bounded by the Tiptap input's own width) |

All three assume the same per-row index suffix (`0`, `1`, `2`...) as generated by
"Current cell's index" in the Repeating Group.

---

## Setup checklist (Bubble side)

1. Tiptap input element → ID Attribute = `tiptap-proposal-[Current cell's index]`
2. Your custom menu element (Group/element containing the format buttons) → ID
   Attribute = `bubble-menu-tiptap-proposal-[Current cell's index]`
3. Each format button → keep its existing Bubble workflow that applies formatting to
   the Tiptap element's selected text (Bold, Italic, Heading, etc.) — **no changes
   needed there**, this script does not touch or interfere with those workflows.
4. In the Tiptap plugin's own element inspector, set **Bubble Menu = "no"** (the
   plugin's native built-in mechanism should stay off, since this script fully
   replaces it).
5. Paste the script from `huzlly-tiptap-rg-bubble-menu-v3.html` into an HTML element
   on the page (once per page, not per row).

